# DOMPURIFY.sanitize()

DOMPURIFY.sanitize() is a function from the DOMPurify library, which is used to sanitize HTML and prevent XSS (Cross-Site Scripting) attacks. It takes potentially unsafe HTML input and returns a sanitized version of it, ensuring that only safe elements and attributes are retained. This function is crucial for web applications that need to render user-generated content securely.

